casebody.data:
The AMERICAN LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY, a Corporation, v. Ole LARSON and Jens Hansen, Stockholders of The American Life Insurance Company, et al. No. 1363. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit Oct. 31, 1935. Emory L. O’Connell and John T. Adams, both of Denver, Colo., for appellant. Erskine R. Myer, of Denver, Colo., for appellees.

Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS, and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed, for failure to prosecute.
